// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// VERCEL PRO FALLBACK — NOT ACTIVE.
//
// We use a free EXTERNAL cron (cron-job.org) to fire the reminder endpoint,
// because the Vercel HOBBY plan only allows ONE cron run PER DAY — and adding a
// sub-daily cron to a real `vercel.json` will FAIL every deploy on Hobby.
//
// If you ever upgrade to Vercel Pro, you can drop the cron config below into a
// file literally named `vercel.json` (rename this file, strip these comments —
// JSON can't have comments) to let Vercel run it natively. Vercel automatically
// sends `Authorization: Bearer ${CRON_SECRET}` when the CRON_SECRET env var is
// set, which the endpoint already checks. Vercel Cron uses GET (the route
// supports both GET and POST).
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{
  "$schema": "https://openapi.vercel.sh/vercel.json",
  "crons": [
    {
      "path": "/api/cron/appointment-reminders",
      "schedule": "*/10 * * * *"
    }
  ]
}
